    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type of weave, primarily used in basketweaving, that consists of alternating splints of plant fiber. Starting at the base, the splints construct one full basket before bending downward to form another basket on the outside of the first.</Note_Text>
